<h1>Your First Program</h1>

<p>
Here are several examples to show you the basic structure of a java program.
</p>

<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
  public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello, World - line 1");
        System.out.println("Hello, World - line 2");
    }
}
</pre>

<p>Here is the same program with comments</p>

<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
  /* 
     Author:   Sir Waddington
     Date:     July 25, 2013
     Revision: 0
  */

  public class HelloWorld {                                // start of program named Hello World
    public static void main(String[] args) {                 // start of main
        System.out.println("Hello, World - line 1");           // first line to be run
        System.out.println("Hello, World - line 2");           // second line to be run
    }                                                                        // end of main
}                                                                        // end of program named Hello World
</pre>

Here is the sort of pattern you should use for your programs:

<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
  public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // 1.  Declare and assign variables here.  (Think of these as the input information your program needs
        // 2.  Do calculations
        // 3.  Display results.  (Think of this as the output of your program).
    }
}
</pre>

